posts.subject: Texture mapping of Pluto surface
posts.body:
Texture mapping can be used with good results also in other fields than radiology to evaluate textures! For example here i used LifeX software to study the pic of Pluto taken by the New Horizon spaceprobe.  Different regions of this dwarf planet appear to have different indicators intensities, as described below. I added also an annotated map of Pluto as reference, the original pic and all the complete data of this experiment in a .zip file. This pic was created by using a low definition color pic and an high definition B/W pic fused together, because of this color don't influence the results. Only elaborations done on red pic will be shown below, the others are included in the zip file.

Original pic from: https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasas-three-billion-mile-journey-to-pluto-reaches-historic-encounter/

posts.subject: Materials and methods
posts.body: LifeX software was used to calculate the local texture maps, GIMP was used to decompose the pic in the RGB component. Local texture maps was calculated by using a 7 px diameter kernel and the full range of grays allowed by png file format (0 to 256) with a size of bin egual to 4 (64 gray levels). Maps were evaluated by using the annotated map to localize the different level of the indicators

posts.subject: GLCM Dissimilarity
posts.body: This indicator is higher in more inhomogeneous regions, because of this Sputnik Planitia, Cthtulhu Regio and  Krun Macula are the darker regions of all the planet, while small craters, the west mountains and the Viking Terra appear redder due to high levels of this indicator. High artefactual values of this indicators appear also to these regions border. The rest of the planet show average levels of this indicator
posts.files: [{"name":"GLCM Dissimilarity.png","thumb":"2255e4893c80ebe17a206c24d7db20cd717ee3c2-thumb.png","size":175494,"type":"image/png","original":"2255e4893c80ebe17a206c24d7db20cd717ee3c2.png","directory":"1GWdvPmMDrhmk6hfX315bBZdhP9vMm8jjM"}]

posts.subject: GLCM Entropy
posts.body: GLCM Entropy is higher in more inhomogeneous regions, as GLCM Dissimilarity, but is calculated by using a different formula. More intense region extend from west mountains to Pandemonium Dorsa, including the western portions of Tombaugh Regio. Areas with high values of GLCM Dissimilarity show also higher GLCM Entropy. Voyager and Pioneer Terras show lower values while Hayabusa Terra shows intermediate values. Sputnik Planitia and the western portion of Tombaugh Regio appear very hypointense
posts.files: [{"name":"GLCM Entropy.png","thumb":"86724f5998364766903bc9250e10134c92b3eb7b-thumb.png","size":219893,"type":"image/png","original":"86724f5998364766903bc9250e10134c92b3eb7b.png","directory":"1GWdvPmMDrhmk6hfX315bBZdhP9vMm8jjM"}]

posts.subject: GLCM Contrast
posts.body: GLCM contrast is calculated with a formula not too different from GLCM Dissimilarity, and because of this shows the same things
posts.files: [{"name":"GLCM Contrast.png","thumb":"934effc485eebcf073c96ba47a4e98a0df36d153-thumb.png","size":106574,"type":"image/png","original":"934effc485eebcf073c96ba47a4e98a0df36d153.png","directory":"1GWdvPmMDrhmk6hfX315bBZdhP9vMm8jjM"}]

posts.subject: GLCM Energy
posts.body: This indicator is higher in homogeneos areas, and is calculated using the reverse formula of GLCM Entropy; because of this shows specular results. Sputnik Planitia, Cthtulhu Regio e Krun Macula appears very intennse, but not in an homogeneous way (high resolution maps of this regions explain why). Voyager and PIoneer Terras show intermediate values, while the others regions of the planet appears hypointense
posts.files: [{"name":"GLCM Energy.png","thumb":"b2511eab6b04bc8690fa888ceca7f0e1158a45a1-thumb.png","size":199870,"type":"image/png","original":"b2511eab6b04bc8690fa888ceca7f0e1158a45a1.png","directory":"1GWdvPmMDrhmk6hfX315bBZdhP9vMm8jjM"}]

posts.subject: GLCM Homogeneity
posts.body: Also in this case Sputnik Planitia (with some eastern regions), Cthtulhu Regio, Krun Macula and Voyager terra appear very intense. Pioneer Terra shows intermediate values, while Hayabusa Terra shows  intermediate-low values. Western regions from Viking Terra appear hypointense. The rest o the planet shows intermediate-low levels of this indicator
